Name:
* Izzat Artykov disqualified for doping according to CAS (Court of Arbitration for Sport) decision of 18 August 2016. 




Men's Lightweight - Weightlifting - Rio 2016 Summer Olympics
Event Format:
     
     In weightlifting the total score for a lifter was the sum of the lifter's result in the snatch and the clean & jerk categories. Three lifts was allowed in each category. In case of a tie, the lighter lifter won. Lifters without a valid snatch score did not perform the clean & jerk category. Event facts: Men's Lightweight competition was held at the Riocentro - Pavilion 2 and 21 athletes participated in the event.

Name:
* Zbigniew Kaczmarek POL disqualified for doping. 




Men's Lightweight - Weightlifting - Montreal 1976 Summer Olympics
Event Format:
     
     Athletes competed in two types of lift: the snatch, in which they raised the bar over the head in one movement, and the clean & jerk, in which they raised the bar i two movements using the combined strength of arms and legs. Each athlete was allowed three attempts at each type of lift. The best result in each type of lift counted in the final score for the athlete.  Event facts: Men's Lightweight competition was held at the St. Michel Arena and 23 athletes participated in the event.

Men's Lightweight - Weightlifting - Munich 1972 Summer Olympics
Event Format:
     
     Athletes competed in three types of lift: the snatch, in which they raised the bar over the head in one movement, the clean & jerk, in which they raised the bar i two movements using the combined strength of arms and legs, and the press, in which they lifted the bar to the shoulders and then over the head using only the arms. Each athlete was allowed three attempts at each type of lift. The best result in each type of lift counted in the final score for the athlete.  Event facts: Men's Lightweight competition was held at the Messegelände and 22 athletes participated in the event.
